                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Dawson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-12-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Strongly advisé President to avoid rupture with cabinet. We are not willing to
                    give instructions to admiral based on assumption that Vice-President and cabinet
                    will create situation requiring our intervention for the protection of American
                    citizens.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
